  <h3>5.8 Disclosure Lag Distribution</h3>
  <p>Most trades are disclosed within 21 days, well within the 45-day STOCK Act maximum. However, outliers persist—notably Tommy Tuberville's BABA and AAPL sales filed <strong>225+ days late</strong>. The mean disclosure lag is <strong>25.0 days</strong> (median: 18.5 days), with a range of 10 to 242 days.</p>
</section>

<!-- 06 Simulator -->
<section id="simulator" class="fade-in">
  <div class="section-num">Section 06</div>
  <h2>Interactive Portfolio Simulator</h2>
  <p>Model expected excess returns at different lag horizons, based on actual lag decay curves from our 68-trade dataset. The confidence band reflects ±1 standard error (σ&thinsp;/&thinsp;√n) of observed returns.</p>

  <div class="simulator">
    <div class="sim-grid">
      <div class="sim-controls">
        <div class="control-group">
          <label>Disclosure Lag (Days)</label>
          <input type="range" id="sim-lag" min="0" max="90" value="30" step="5" oninput="updateSimulator()">
          <div class="range-val" id="sim-lag-val">T+30 days</div>
        </div>
        <div class="control-group">
          <label>Trade Type</label>
          <div class="checkbox-group">
