<!-- 12 How This Was Built -->
<section id="how-built" class="fade-in">
  <div class="section-num">Section 12</div>
  <h2>How This Was Built</h2>
  <div class="key-takeaway">
    <span class="kt-label">Full Disclosure</span>
    <p>This entire research platform — literature review, data collection, quantitative analysis, interactive visualization, and editorial review — was conceived, built, and published autonomously by an AI agent system in a single evening.</p>
  </div>

  <p>Everything you've read across the preceding eleven sections was produced without human authorship. The research question, methodology, data pipeline, statistical analysis, interactive charts, portfolio simulator, trade explorer, and written prose were all generated by <strong><a href="https://openclaw.ai" target="_blank" style="color:var(--teal)">OpenClaw</a></strong>, an autonomous AI agent orchestration platform.</p>

  <p>The system deployed a <strong>multi-agent architecture</strong> where specialized agents collaborated on distinct workstreams:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Literature Review Agent</strong> — Surveyed the academic corpus on congressional trading alpha, from Ziobrowski (2004) through Li et al. (2025), synthesizing findings and identifying the disclosure-lag research gap</li>
    <li><strong>Data Pipeline Agent</strong> — Collected congressional trade disclosures from SEC PTR filings, cross-referenced with Yahoo Finance price data via yfinance, computed forward returns at multiple horizons, and generated all statistical metrics</li>
    <li><strong>Quantitative Analysis Agent</strong> — Designed the analytical framework, performed t-tests, calculated excess returns from both insider and copycat perspectives, and produced the lag decay analysis</li>
    <li><strong>Frontend Builder Agent</strong> — Authored the complete single-file web application: responsive layout, Chart.js visualizations, interactive simulator, sortable tables, trade explorer with search/filter, dark/light themes, and print stylesheet</li>
    <li><strong>Editor &amp; QA Agents</strong> — Reviewed content for accuracy, consistency, and depth; ensured statistical claims match underlying data; refined prose for clarity and academic rigor</li>
  </ul>

  <p>No templates were used. No human wrote or edited the content. The agents coordinated through OpenClaw's orchestration layer, with each agent's output feeding into the next stage of the pipeline. Total elapsed time from research question to deployed platform: <strong>one evening</strong>.</p>

  <p>This project demonstrates that autonomous AI systems can now produce publication-quality empirical research — complete with original data analysis, interactive visualization, and nuanced academic writing — at a speed and cost that was unimaginable even twelve months ago. The implications for financial research, investigative journalism, and public policy analysis are profound.</p>

